N:sprint-retrospective
D:Facilitate sprint retrospectives, milestone postmortems, or iteration reviews that turn completed work into a few owned process improvements instead of another stale template exercise. Use when the user needs a retro format, async or hybrid retro flow, retrospective facilitation script, or action follow-through after a sprint, release, milestone, or rough delivery cycle.
G:sprint-retrospective retrospective milestone-review postmortem-lite team-improvement facilitation

U[5]:
  Run a retrospective after a sprint, milestone, release push, or rough delivery cycle
  Choose a lightweight retro mode instead of defaulting to a stale template
  Review prior action items before creating new ones
  Support async or hybrid retrospective facilitation
  Return a concise packet with signals, actions, and a next move

X[4]:
  future-work planning or backlog slicing -> task-planning
  story points, t-shirt sizes, or forecast ranges -> task-estimation
  daily status cadence or blocker rounds -> standup-meeting
  deep incident forensics or log triage -> debugging or log-analysis

S[5]{n,action}:
  1,Identify the retrospective mode
  2,Review prior actions before inventing new ones
  3,Choose the lightest useful retrospective format
  4,Distill evidence into themes and a tiny action set
  5,Return the retrospective packet

R[5]:
  completed-work review stays separate from planning and estimation
  previous commitments are reviewed before new actions are added
  action lists stay small and owner-backed
  unresolved technical forensics are routed instead of hand-waved
  output ends with a recommended next move
